story.storykicker: Here is the list of important documents that you will need to carry for counseling, once you clear the AIIMS MBBS 2016 examination.
story.storybody:
All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS) recently conducted an entrance examination for candidates seeking admission in its MBBS course.

The results of AIIMS, MBBS 2016 examination is expected to be declared on June 14, 2016.

The esteemed institute will be holding three rounds of counseling for students seeking an admission in the MBBS course.

Schedule of counseling:

  • First counseling will be held on July 4, 5 and 6, 2016
  • Second round of counseling will be held on August 4, 2016
  • The third round is scheduled for September 6, 2016
  • In case the need arises, open counseling will be conducted on September 27, 2016
The selected candidates should ensure that they carry the following documents on the dates of counseling:
  • AIIMS MBBS Admit Card
  • Call letter issued by AIIMS, New Delhi
  • Date of Birth, Certificate/ Mark sheet from the board which shows that the candidates have passed the 10+2
  • Migration certificate from the University/Board last attended by the candidate
  • Category certificate (If applicable)
  • 6 passport size photographs
  • One set of self-attested copies of all the certificates.
The AIIMS MBBS entrance exam was conducted successfully on May 29, 2016.

 

About AIIMS

All-India Institute of Medical Sciences was established as an institution of national importance by an Act of Parliament with the objects to develop patterns of teaching in undergraduate and post-graduate Medical education in all its branches, so as to demonstrate a high standard of Medical Education in India; to bring together the educational facilities of the highest order for the training of personnel in all important branches of health activity; and to attain self-sufficiency in post-graduate Medical education.

 

For any query, the candidates should visit the official website.

For more updates, follow India Today Education.
